Third-party data sources (online IME lexicon build)
===================================================

This repository may include or reference the following projects when
building browser IME lexicons (`npm run ime:build-lexicons`):

1. jyutcitzi-RIME (git submodule: `submodules/jyutcitzi-RIME`)
   https://github.com/cantonese-jyutcitzi/jyutcitzi-RIME
   See that repository for license terms.

2. rime-cantonese (git submodule: `submodules/rime-cantonese`)
   https://github.com/rime/rime-cantonese
   See that repository for license terms (e.g. CC BY 4.0 for dictionary data).

3. jyutcitzi-transliterate (git submodule: `transliteration/vendor/jyutcitzi-transliterate`)
   https://github.com/cantonese-jyutcitzi/jyutcitzi-transliterate
   See that repository for license terms.

The `/tools/ime` page is a separate, browser-only product and does not ship
the upstream YAML verbatim; it uses compiled binary assets produced locally
from those sources. The online IME UI may link to upstream READMEs for
power users.

Build fidelity note (v1): the compiler follows `import_tables` merge order
from `jyutcitzi_web.dict.yaml` / `jyutcitzi_font.dict.yaml`. Full parity with
all Rime `use_preset_vocabulary` and preset vocabulary behaviour is not
guaranteed in v1; see `frontend/scripts/ime/README.md`.
